# Interactive Cubic Bézier Rope (Web)

## Overview
Cubic Bézier curve that behaves like a springy rope. Middle control points move dynamically via mouse, touch, or device tilt.

## Math
- Bézier: B(t) = (1-t)^3 P0 + 3(1-t)^2 t P1 + 3(1-t) t^2 P2 + t^3 P3
- Tangent: B'(t) = 3(1-t)^2 (P1-P0) + 6(1-t)t (P2-P1) + 3 t^2 (P3-P2)

## Physics
- Spring-damper: a = (-k*(pos-target) - damping*vel)/mass
- Semi-implicit Euler integration for smooth motion.

## Interaction
- Mouse: drag P1/P2 or whole rope.
- Touch: move both points.
- Reset: press R key.

## Rendering
- Curve: green
- Control points: yellow
- Tangents: blue

## Files
- interactive_bezier_rope.html — source code
- rope_demo.mp4 — 20–30s screen recording
